rig-core's Ollama agent uses the **`/api/chat` endpoint**, which sends structured messages (`role: "user"`, etc.). Ollama then applies the correct chat template for whatever model is loaded — Qwen, Llama, Mistral, etc. The embedded `<|system|>` tokens in the prompt are now treated as plain text inside a user message rather than conflicting with the chat format.

